verbs.description: manumise (third-person singular simple present manumises, present participle manumising, simple past and past participle manumised)

entries.meaning: (transitive, obsolete) To manumit. [16th to early 19th c.]
examples: […]  it were a charytable dede to euery noble man  […]  to manumise them that be bonde and to make them free of body and blode
